The paper discusses the potential of device-to-device (D2D) communication for next-generation cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper uses stochastic geometry and Poisson point process, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the impact of path-loss and distance criteria, which are relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR).
